Description: Typical range for 1064 nm ns-pulsed lasers in industrial cleaning of Ti-6Al-4V to remove contaminants without excessive heating; starting at 100 W for light oxidation, max limited by low thermal conductivity (6.7 W/m·K) to avoid melting (1660°C); source: CleanLaser CL 1000 manual and study in Optics and Lasers in Engineering (2018) on Ti alloys.
Near-IR wavelength for optimal metal absorption
Beam spot diameter for effective cleaning resolution
Pulse duration for minimal heat-affected zone
Beam travel speed for uniform treatment
Number of cleaning cycles for complete removal
